---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "About UlamPinoy | The Filipino Family Kitchen Chronicles";
const pageDescription =
  "Meet the family behind UlamPinoy, sharing authentic Filipino recipes and kitchen stories from our home in Spain to yours.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="bg-white pt-16 pb-16">
    {/* Hero Section */}
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-white py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h1
            class="savate-heavy text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-amber-600 mb-6"
          >
            Kumusta Kaibigan! ðŸ‘‹
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            We're a Filipino family living in Spain, cooking our way through
            homesickness one recipe at a time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="md:w-1/2 p-6 md:p-12 flex flex-col justify-center">
              <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Our Epic Journey
              </h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Ulampinoy started as our digital recipe diary and somehow
                evolved into a full-blown family project where we cook together,
                learn from each other, and share our culinary adventures one
                recipe at a time.
              </p>
              <div class="flex gap-4">
                <a
                  href="/"
                  class="w-full px-6 py-3 bg-amber-500 text-white rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors"
                >
                  What's New?
                </a>
                <a
                  href="/videos"
                  class="w-full px-6 py-3 border-2 border-amber-500 text-amber-600 rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors"
                >
                  Watch Videos
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 h-64 md:h-auto bg-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
              <img
                src="/images/eggplant-stove.jpg"
                alt="Fresh eggplants on a stove in a Filipino kitchen"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Origin Story */}
    <section id="our-story" class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 tracking-wider font-medium"
            >ORIGIN STORY</span
          >
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            The Manila-Madrid Connection
          </h2>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600">
          <p>
            Once upon a time, we migrated to Spain and realized that decent
            Filipino food was rarer than parking spaces in Madrid. Like millions
            of Filipinos around the world, we're part of the beautiful diaspora
            that carries our culture, traditions, and most importantly, our
            recipes wherever we go.
          </p>
          <div class="m-w-full">
            <iframe
              src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d47842858.82403228!2d28.054299243485257!3d18.351996414516027!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e4!4m5!1s0x3397c8d26026386d%3A0x5fed23daac9278d0!2sManila%2C%20Philippines!3m2!1d14.609053699999999!2d121.0222565!4m5!1s0xd422997800a3c81%3A0xc436dec1618c2269!2sMadrid%2C%20Spain!3m2!1d40.4167279!2d-3.7032905!5e0!3m2!1sen!2ses!4v1749459830317!5m2!1sen!2ses"
              width="100%"
              height="480"
              style="border:0;"
              allowfullscreen="false"
              loading="lazy"
              referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe>
          </div>
          <p>
            There's something beautifully full-circle about the Manila-Madrid
            connection â€“ centuries of shared history through colonial ties and
            cultural exchange, and now here we are, modern Filipinos in Spain
            sharing our heritage through kitchen stories and YouTube videos. So
            we did what any sensible Filipino family would do: we started
            cooking everything ourselves
          </p>
          <p>
            So we did what any sensible Filipino family would do: we started
            cooking everything ourselves and documenting it obsessively. What
            began as a simple food journal quickly transformed into our <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/user/ulampinoy/featured"
              class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium"
              >YouTube cooking channel</a
            > â€“ a family project that serves as journal and a way to bond.
          </p>

          <p>
            Every recipe comes with stories, memories, and the occasional
            kitchen disaster (which we may or may not include in the final cut).
            You can find all our <a
              href="/videos"
              class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium"
              >video recipes</a
            > organized by category, or if you're scratching your head wondering
            what "gata" or "patis" means, our handy
            <a
              href="/glossary"
              class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium"
              >glossary</a
            > has got your back with translations and explanations of Filipino cooking
            terms.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Mission Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 tracking-wide font-medium"
            >OUR MISSION</span
          >
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            More Than Just Recipes
          </h2>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600">
          <p>
            We're building the ultimate Filipino family cookbook, one video at a
            time. Our goal is simple: create a collection of tried-and-tested
            recipes with our own family twist, presented in a way that won't put
            you to sleep (unlike your typical cooking show).
          </p>

          <p>
            Beyond recipes, we share discoveries, lessons learned, random
            kitchen wisdom, and whatever else catches our fancy in our <a
              href="/articles"
              class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-800 font-medium"
              >articles section</a
            >. Think of us as your Filipino cooking uncles and titas who happen
            to live in Spain and know way too much about proper rice-to-water
            ratios.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Tech Stack Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="text-amber-500 tracking-wide font-medium"
            >UNDER THE HOOD</span
          >
          <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-gray-900 mt-2">
            Behind the Scenes
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">
            How we use web tech to craft and ship this website with love and
            umami
          </p>
          <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-amber-400 mx-auto mt-4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Tech Stack</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">â€¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">AstroJS</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                    Because we upgraded from Eleventy and now our build times
                    are faster than cooking minute rice
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">â€¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Netlify</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                    Our deployment heroes who keep us online (salamat!)
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">â€¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">GitHub</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                    Where our code lives and where we backup our digital kitchen
                    secrets
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-amber-500 mr-3 mt-1">â€¢</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900">Google Fonts</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                    Making our text look prettier than our food photography
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-amber-50 p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
              What's in a Name?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              If you're wondering about the name <strong>"Ulampinoy,"</strong> it's
              a portmanteau of "ulam" (Filipino for viand/main dish) and "Pinoy"
              (colloquial term for Filipino). Yes, we're that creative with our naming
              conventions.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                Ulam PInoy YouTube Channel Stats
              </h3>
              <p>
                <strong>66.4K+ subscribers</strong> and over 11,321,995 video views
                from our 131 videos and counting!
              </p>
              <p>Apparently, we're not the only ones who miss home cooking!</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* CTA Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-amber-600 text-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
        <h2 class="savate-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">
          Let's Cook Together!
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-amber-100">
          Have a recipe request? Want to argue about the proper way to cook
          adobo? Just want to say hi? We'd love to hear from you!
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-full text-amber-700 bg-white hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors"
          >
            Get in Touch
          </a>
          <a
            href="/videos"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border-2 border-white text-base font-medium rounded-full text-white hover:bg-white hover:bg-opacity-10 transition-colors"
          >
            Watch Our Videos
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
